type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>. In other words, we must show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathsf {isTruncated}\,  \mathopen {}\left \lparen n-1\right \rparen \mathclose {} \,A]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>. By our inductive hypothesis, this is a dependent product of <fr:link
